<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2646/98 of 9 December 1998 laying down detailed rules for the implementation of Council Regulation (EC) No 2494/95 as regards minimum standards for the treatment of tariffs in the Harmonized Index of Consumer Prices (Text with EEA relevance) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2646/98, millega kehtestatakse &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 rakendamiseks &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksi hinnaloendite k&auml;sitlemise miinimumstandardite kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 9. detsember 1998 (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2494/95 of 23 October 1995 concerning harmonised indices of consumer prices (1), and in particular Articles 4 and 5(3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. oktoobri 1995. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksite kohta, (1) eriti selle artiklit 4 ja artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> After consulting the European Central Bank (2), </inglise>
<eesti> olles n&otilde;u pidanud Euroopa Keskpangaga (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by virtue of Article 5(1) (b) of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95, each Member State is required to produce a Harmonized Index of Consumer Prices (HICP) starting with the index for January 1997; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti b kohaselt peab iga liikmesriik koostama &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksi (&Uuml;THI) alates 1997. aasta jaanuari indeksist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 9 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95 requires to ensure that the Laspeyres-type index formula is applied consistently to all sub-indices or categories of expenditure concerned; whereas their weights should reflect appropriately the pattern of expenditure by the index population; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artikli 9 kohaselt tuleb tagada, et Laspeyrese t&uuml;&uuml;pi valemit kohaldatakse j&auml;rjepidevalt k&otilde;ikide asjakohaste osaindeksite v&otilde;i kululiikide suhtes; nende kaalud peaksid asjakohaselt kajastama indeksi &uuml;ldkogumi kulutusharjumusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas HICP sub-indices involving tariff prices are, in practice, either obtained directly from suppliers or computed by the Members States based on data on tariff prices and their underlying consumption patterns provided by suppliers; whereas there is considerable scope for procedural differences in the construction of sub-indices where changes in the structure of tariffs are made at the same time as changes are made to the tariff price of a particular element to the extent that consumers are obliged to make new choices in their consumption; whereas it is therefore important to ensure that the relevant basic information can be obtained as to ensure that the resulting HICPs do not fail to meet the comparability requirement of Article 4 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95; </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;THI osaindeksid, mis h&otilde;lmavad loendihindu, saadakse tegelikult otse tarnijatelt v&otilde;i nii, et liikmesriigid arvutavad need tarnijate edastatud andmete p&otilde;hjal, mis k&auml;sitlevad loendihindu ja nende aluseks olevaid tarbimisharjumusi; osaindeksite koostamise viisid v&otilde;ivad olla v&auml;ga erinevad, kui muutusi hinnaloendite koosseisus tehakse samal ajal kui muutusi teatava koostisosa loendihinnas, mist&otilde;ttu tarbijad peavad muutma oma tarbimisharjumusi; seep&auml;rast on vaja tagada, et saadaks asjakohaseid alusandmeid, et olla veendunud koostatavate &Uuml;THIde vastavuses m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artikli 4 v&otilde;rreldavusn&otilde;udele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by virtue of Article 6 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95, the basic information for the production of HICPs which should be obtained from the statistical units, consists of those prices and weights which it is necessary to take into account in order to achieve comparability; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2494/95 artikli 6 kohaselt koosnevad &Uuml;THIde koostamiseks kasutatavad statistilistest &uuml;ksustest saadavad alusandmed nendest hindadest ja kaaludest, mida on vaja arvesse v&otilde;tta v&otilde;rreldavuse saavutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by virtue of Article 7 of Regulation (EC) No 2494/95, the statistical units called upon by the Member States to cooperate in the collection or provision of price data should be obliged to allow observation of the prices actually charged and to give honest and complete information at the time it is requested; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2492/95 artikli 7 kohaselt on statistilised &uuml;ksused, kelle poole liikmesriigid p&ouml;&ouml;rduvad koost&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks hinnateabe kogumisel v&otilde;i esitamisel, kohustatud lubama vaadelda tegelikult kehtivaid hindu ning andma &otilde;igeid ja t&auml;ielikke andmeid siis, kui neid n&otilde;utakse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas by virtue of Article 4 of Commission Regulation (EC) No 1749/96 (3), as last amended by Council Regulation (EC) No 1688/98 (4), the HICP should be compiled to include the price changes of a newly significant good or service; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1749/96 (3) (viimati muudetud n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1688/98 (4)) artikli 4 kohaselt tuleks &Uuml;THI koostada nii, et see sisaldaks uute oluliste teenuste ja kaupade hinnamuutusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Regulation should not require Member States to carry out new statistical surveys; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega ei tohiks liikmesriikidelt n&otilde;uda uute statistiliste vaatluste tegemist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Statistical Programme Committee (SPC), </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las statistikaprogrammi komitee (SPK) arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Aim </inglise>
<eesti> Eesm&auml;rk </eesti>
<inglise> The aim of this Regulation is to set down minimum standards for the treatment of 'tariff prices' in the Harmonized Index of Consumer Prices (HICP). </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse eesm&auml;rk on kehtestada &uuml;htlustatud tarbijahinnaindeksi (&Uuml;THI) loendihindade k&auml;sitlemise miinimumstandardid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this Regulation: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. a tariff is a list of pre-established prices and conditions for the purchase and consumption of one and the same good or service or of similar goods and services that has been centrally fixed by the supplier, by the government, or by agreement to exert influence on the consumption patterns by means of appropriately differentiated prices and conditions according to characteristics of consumers, the level, the structure or the timing of the consumption. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. hinnaloend - &uuml;he ja sama kauba v&otilde;i teenuse v&otilde;i sarnaste kaupade v&otilde;i teenuste ostmiseks ja tarbimiseks eelnevalt m&auml;&auml;ratud hindade ja tingimuste loend, mille on &uuml;ldkohaldatavalt kinnitanud tarnija v&otilde;i riik v&otilde;i mis on s&auml;testatud kokkuleppes, et sobivalt eristatud hindade ja tingimuste abil m&otilde;jutada tarbijate tunnusjoontest, tarbimistasemest, -struktuurist v&otilde;i -hetkest s&otilde;ltuvaid tarbimisharjumusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Tariffs are not negotiable for households; </inglise>
<eesti> Leibkondadele hinnaloendeid ei kinnitata; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. a tariff price is a price within a tariff that applies to a component element or unit of consumption of the good or service in question. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. loendihind - hinnaloendis sisalduv hind, mida kohaldatakse hinnaloendi koostisosa v&otilde;i asjakohase kauba v&otilde;i teenuse tarbimis&uuml;hiku suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Basic information </inglise>
<eesti> Alusandmed </eesti>
<inglise> The basic information shall be all tariff prices and weights which reflect the structure of the consumption of the good or services according to the characteristics of the consumers, the level, the structure or the timing of the consumption. </inglise>
<eesti> Alusandmeteks on k&otilde;ik loendihinnad ja -kaalud, mis kajastavad kaupade v&otilde;i teenuste tarbimise struktuuri s&otilde;ltuvalt tarbijate tunnusjoontest, tarbimistasemest, -struktuurist v&otilde;i -hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Data sources </inglise>
<eesti> Teabeallikad </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> HICP sub-indices involving tariff prices shall be computed by the Member States from basic information as defined in Article 3 provided by the supplier. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid arvutavad loendihindu sisaldavad &Uuml;THI osaindeksid tarnijate esitatud alusandmete p&otilde;hjal, mis on m&auml;&auml;ratletud artiklis 3. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The statistical units called upon by the Member States to cooperate in the collection or provision of basic information are obliged to give honest and complete information at the time it is requested and allow the organisations and institutions responsible for compiling official statistics at their request to obtain information at the level of detail necessary to evaluate compliance with the comparability requirements and the quality of the HICP sub-indices. </inglise>
<eesti> Statistilised &uuml;ksused, kelle poole liikmesriigid p&ouml;&ouml;rduvad koost&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks hinnateabe kogumisel v&otilde;i esitamisel, on kohustatud andma &otilde;igeid ja t&auml;ielikke andmeid siis, kui neid n&otilde;utakse, ja v&otilde;imaldama ametliku statistika koostamise eest vastutavatel organisatsioonidel ja asutustel n&otilde;udmise korral hankida v&otilde;rreldavusn&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise ja &Uuml;THI osaindeksite kvaliteedi hindamiseks piisavalt &uuml;ksikasjalikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Procedure </inglise>
<eesti> Menetlus </eesti>
<inglise> HICP sub-indices involving tariff prices shall be calculated using a formula which is consistent with the Laspeyres-type formula used for other sub-indices. </inglise>
<eesti> Loendihindu sisaldavad &Uuml;THI osaindeksid arvutatakse muude osaindeksite puhul kasutatava Laspeyrese t&uuml;&uuml;pi valemiga. </eesti>
<inglise> They should reflect the price change on the basis of the changed expenditure of maintaining that consumption pattern chosen by households prior to the given change in the tariff. </inglise>
<eesti> Osaindeksid peaksid kajastama hinnamuutusi, mis p&otilde;hinevad kulutuste muutustel, mis leibkonnad on valitud tarbimusharjumuste j&auml;tkamiseks teinud enne asjakohast hinnaloendi muutust. </eesti>
<inglise> Where there is a change in the tariff and where, after that change: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui hinnaloend muutub ja kui p&auml;rast seda muutust: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. a component element or a unit of consumption remains unchanged with respect to its specification, then the price for that element or unit according to the old and the new tariff shall be directly compared and the price difference taken into the HICP; </inglise>
<eesti> 1. hinnaloendi koostisosa v&otilde;i tarbimis&uuml;hiku tunnusjooned j&auml;&auml;vad samaks, siis v&otilde;rreldakse selle koostisosa v&otilde;i &uuml;hiku hinda uues ja vanas hinnaloendis otseselt ning hinnamuutus arvatakse &Uuml;THIsse; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. a component element or a unit of consumption changes with respect to its specification, or a new component element is added which does not constitute a new good or service for the consumer, then the price change shall be computed with weights corresponding to the expenditure of preserving the pattern of consumption applying during a period, up to one year, preceding the change. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. hinnaloendi koostisosa muutub v&otilde;i muutuvad tarbimis&uuml;hiku tunnusjooned v&otilde;i lisandub uus koostisosa, mis ei ole tarbijale uus kaup ega teenus, arvutatakse hinnamuutus, kaaludes neid kulusid, mis vastavad muutusele eelnenud ja k&otilde;ige rohkem aastasel ajavahemikul t&auml;heldatud tarbimisharjumuse s&auml;ilitamise kulule. </eesti>
<inglise> The adjustments for specification changes shall be consistent with quality adjustments made for other sub-indices; </inglise>
<eesti> Tunnusjoonte muutumisega seotud kohandused peavad olema koosk&otilde;las muudes osaindeksites tehtud kvaliteedikohandustega; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. a component element or a unit of consumption with a new and distinct specification constituting a new good or service for the consumer is added to the tariff, it shall be treated as 'newly significant goods and services' as defined in Regulation (EC) No 1749/96. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. lisatakse hinnaloendisse koostisosa v&otilde;i tarbimis&uuml;hik, millel on uued ja erilised tunnusjooned ja mis on tarbijale uus kaup v&otilde;i teenus, k&auml;sitletakse seda m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 1749/96 m&auml;&auml;ratletud "uue olulise kauba v&otilde;i teenusena". </eesti>
<inglise> If the expenditure on the new good or service is significant it shall be taken into the index by linking from the month when the new tariff comes into force using an estimate of expected immediate consumption or within a period of 12 months otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kulutused uuele kaubale v&otilde;i teenusele on m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rsed, arvatakse need indeksisse uue hinnaloendi j&otilde;ustumise kuust, eeldades kas kohest tarbimist v&otilde;i tarbimist 12kuulisel ajavahemikul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Comparability </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;rreldavus </eesti>
<inglise> HICPs constructed following the procedures described in Article 5 of this Regulation or following other procedures which do not result in an index which differs systematically by more than one-tenth of one percentage point on average over one year against the previous year from an index compiled following those procedures, shall be deemed comparable. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;rreldavad on &Uuml;THId, mis on koostatud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 5 kirjeldatud menetluse v&otilde;i muude menetluste abil, mille tulemuseks on indeks, mis &uuml;he aasta jooksul j&auml;rjekindlalt ei erine keskmiselt rohkem kui k&uuml;mnendikprotsendi v&otilde;rra nendesamade menetluste abil koostatud eelmise aasta indeksist. </eesti>
<inglise> Any amendments of procedures and practices to secure comparability as defined in this paragraph shall be implemented at the earliest for the sub-indices following the entry into force of this Regulation, and at the latest by December 1998 and take effect with the index for January 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik eelnevas l&otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;ratletud v&otilde;rreldavuse tagamiseks tehtavad muutused menetlustes ja v&otilde;tetes rakendatakse k&otilde;ige varem k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumise j&auml;rel koostatud osaindeksites ja hiljemalt 1998. aasta detsembriks ning need j&otilde;ustuvad 1999. jaanuari indeksist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Quality control </inglise>
<eesti> Kvaliteedikontroll </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall provide the Commission (Eurostat) with information on the procedures developed for the treatment of tariff prices where these procedures differ from those specified in Article 5 of this Regulation, before such procedures are used. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile (Eurostat) teavet loendihindade k&auml;sitlemiseks koostatud menetluste kohta, kui need menetlused erinevad k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 5 piiritletutest, tehes seda enne nende kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall also provide the Commission (Eurostat), on its request, with information on the procedures used for meeting the requirement of minimum standards established in this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti edastavad liikmesriigid komisjonile (Eurostat) viimase n&otilde;udel teavet k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud miinimumstandardite t&auml;itmiseks kasutavate menetluste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Entry into force </inglise>
<eesti> J&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 9 December 1998. For the Commission Yves-Thibault DE SILGUY Member of the Commission </inglise>
